---
import ContentLayout from '@layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
---
<ContentLayout title="Sources" eyebrow="References" description="A place to record references, further reading, and attribution notes as the project grows." breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Sources' }]}>
  <h2>Books</h2>

  <h3>Hapkido: Traditions, Philosophy, Technique — Marc Tedeschi</h3>
  <p>Use this as a reference for terminology, historical context, and cross-checking technique families where possible.</p>
  <p>Technique pages reserve explicit frontmatter placeholders for Tedeschi cross-checking. Leave them blank until verified:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>tedeschi_reference_name</code> — the verified reference name or section.</li>
    <li><code>tedeschi_reference_page</code> — the verified page number or page range.</li>
    <li>Notes on whether the school version differs.</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="callout">Do not add page numbers, quotes, reference names, or equivalence claims unless verified.</p>

  <h2>School and class notes</h2>
  <p>Technique names and sequencing may come from Anthony's school curriculum, class notes, structured writeups, and instructor feedback.</p>

  <h2>Online and video references</h2>
  <p>Use reputable online references with access dates and concise summaries. Use video notes only where attribution and permitted use are clear.</p>

  <h2>Notes on copyright and attribution</h2>
  <p class="callout">Do not copy copyrighted curriculum text or images directly. Summarize, cite, and use original photos, notes, diagrams, or public-domain / licensed assets when possible.</p>
</ContentLayout>
